<p>A true root system consists of a <b>primary root</b> and <b>secondary ro=
ots</b> (or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lateral_roots" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Lateral roots">lateral roots</a>).
</p>
<ul><li>the diffuse root system: the primary root is not dominant; the whol=
e root system is fibrous and branches in all directions. Most common in <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monocots" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Monocots">monocots</a>. The main function of the fibrous root is to anc=
hor the plant.</li></ul>
